Whisk egg whites until frothy; gradually whisk in milk. Set aside. Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and dip in egg white mixture. Dredge in flour, shaking off excess. Cook chicken in hot oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally until chicken is lightly browned. Drain chicken on paper towels. Combine SPLENDA(R) Granulated Sweetener, Sylvia's Secret Seasoning(R), orange juice, 1/2 cup water and ginger in a small saucepan. Bring SPLENDA(R) Granulated Sweetener mixture to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring constantly. Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup water, stirring until cornstarch dissolves; add to SPLENDA(R) Granulated Sweetener mixture, stirring until mixture returns to a boil. Add chicken and cook 2 to 3 minutes. Serve immediately.